Five historiated miniatures are found in the manuscript. On the fragmented f. 1r (a breaking wheel and a killing scene featuring a victim on the left the killer standing behind the victim with a sword on the right; and on f. 72r; f. 81r; f. 85r and f. 90r fighting scenes featuring two (f. 72r; f. 85r) and three (f. 81r; f. 90r) figures. In addition; on f. 93r; the flaggellation of a single figure and the hanging of three figures is depicted. All of these sections refer to the respective sections of the MEL (on homicide and on theft). Otherwise; the manuscript contains fifteen large initials (4 -5 lines) on f. 3r22-26; f. 14v16-22; f. 25v16-21; f. 32r1-5; f. 41v1-4; f. 45v1-4; f. 47v13-16; f. 52r5-8; f. 56v21-24; f. 64r11-16; f. 74r1-4; f. 82r1-4; f. 86r1-4; f. 91r1-4 and f. 95r1-5. In addition; on f. 39r; two ornamented medium initials are found; but it seems they are part of a palimsest as both the featured texts is wiped out and also the featured colours and the style of the paintings are different from the other sections of the manuscript.

The manuscript features four historiated initials; of which the first two are embellished with gold. The historiated initials are on f. 2r4-10 (Konungabalken; ch. 1; Showing a frontally seated and crowned king holding the imperial orb; dressed in green and white); f. 12r1-10 (Edsöresbalk; ch. 1; Showing a frontally seated king holding an open book and a sceptre; flanked by to bishops; all placed in architectural framing); f. 32r1-8 (Vådamål och såramål; ch. 1; A killing scene showing two men fighting with swords. One has lost his head. In the foreground a further figure is depicted looking at the homicide scene); f. 56v8-15 (Ärvdabalken; ch. 1; Showing a dying man in bed in the foreground and two mourning women behind and on the left). In addition; Christ on the cross is depicted in the lower right margin on f. 39v. According to AV; the manuscript contains altogether 22 large initials.
